t</span><hr size=1> I can tell you from experience that this will be the final nail in the coffin for clerics, as far as trying to find exp groups goes.  Unless I get an invite for a group from someone who knows me in whatever zone I'm LFG in, I don't get a group....it's that simple...and those invites are usually pity invites because they've seen me shouting &quot;55 cleric LFG&quot; for the last hour.  People pull streams of low blues for exp purposes, and a cleric's healing ability simply isn't needed for these.  It's even worse when there is a shaman in the group slowing the mobs; it makes me feel like an exp moocher because there's really nothing for me to do, except maybe buff the tanks every hour or so or throw a heal on the casters when they occasionally overnuke and get aggro.  Unless the group is fighting nothing but undead (which rarely happens), cleric nukes don't add enough to the DPS to be useful. In an exp group, there are 3 useful things a cleric can do: heal, buff, rez.  Well, I don't have to worry about heals as it is now...I sure as hell won't have to worry about it if these changes go live.  And rezzing...who the hell dies in an easy exp group when you're pulling stuff 10 steps from the zone? So, that makes me a buff whore...whoopteedoo.<br>
<br>
But clerics are still needed for raids, I hear people saying.  Yeah, that's fun...stare at a wall and mash a button every few seconds. Woohoo...I'm uber now!<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I don't have anything against shaman and druids...well, maybe a few druids.  I understand that druids needed something to help them be more raid friendly, and I'm all for any changes that help them...but not at the cost of a cleric's ability and uniqueness.  Clerics used to be specialists at healing and crap at everything else.  Now, we're 5% better at healing, if that, and STILL crap at everything else.<br>
<br>
If these changes go live, with the numbers they have now on the spells, it will be a sad, sad day for clerics. <p>Velisaris Groovenhymer<BR>
